Minister of Health Dr. Aaron Motsoaledi has appointed an Ad-hoc Independent tribunal to process all appeals relating to Health Ombuds report.The tribunal which will be headed by retired Judge President of the Gauteng High Court Judge Bernard Ngoepe, will focus more on the circumstances surrounding the deaths of mentally ill patients in the province.At least 100 mentally ill patients died after they were transferred from Life Esidimeni to various NGOs last year.Twenty of the 22 unlicensed NGOs, to which the mentally ill patients were originally transferred from Life Esidimeni, are still open.To date, 57 patients have been relocated since the implementation of the Mental Health transfer project. Gauteng Health (@GautengHealth) March 8, 2017We successfully relocated 28 Mental Health Care users to Selby Hospital from Rebafenyi House 3. Gauteng Health (@GautengHealth) March 8, 2017Two licensed institutions namely Selby Hospital &amp; Life Esidimeni Baneng have been appointed. pic.twitter.com/B6lbEE9PPR Gauteng Health (@GautengHealth) March 8, 2017More than 57 patients have been relocated since the implementation of the Mental Health transfer project. With 28 psychiatric patients transferred to Selby Park Hospital in Johannesburg.Gauteng MEC for Health Dr Gwen Ramokgopa during a briefing stated that it costs about R495 per patient per day at the Solomon Stix Morewa Memorial Hospital. The money towards therapy, laundry, food and accommodation.-TNA Reporter